token_lists.title: Project 5am music
token_lists.description: Jason Kofi-Haye created the metaphysical art/philosophy “Project 5am” stimulated by a peak experience during that exact moment in time and the Allen Ginsberg poem ‘Five am’. It was under this banner where Kofi-Haye started to produce a series of interdisciplinary art works. Projects include the electronic album ‘Quixotes of Moons Fight The Windmills of Brixton’ and the experimental short film ‘Some kind of wonderful’ which was one of the films chosen for the Danish film auteur Lars Von Trier community project ‘Gesamt’ at the Copenhagen Art Festival. Project 5am music has featured on  documentaries and web shows and radio stations such as WFMU, Radio Scorpio and Soma FM.
